# Plant Counting Using Python

This project implements a plant counting solution using Python. 
1.  Using OpenCV techniques (color segmentation, morphology, and contour detection) to count plants in an image.

## Features
-  Apply color thresholding and contour detection using OpenCV.
- Easy conversion from GeoTIFF to JPEG (external conversion done).
## Requirements
-python 3.6 recomemended
 The following packages are required:
- pip install opencv-python
- pip install torch torchvision
- pip install numpy
- pip install Pillow



